Harold Lockwood https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harold_Lockwood 0 Harold A. Lockwood (April 12, 1887 – October 19, 1918) was an American silent film actor, director, and producer. He was one of the most popular matinee idols of the early film period during the 1910s.
